```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Dynamic Theme Switching</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="src/styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Dynamic Theme Switcher</h1>
    <button id="theme-toggle">Toggle Theme</button>
    
    <script src="dist/index.js" type="module"></script> <!-- Adjust path as needed -->
</body>
</html>
```
---

### Explanation
1. **Modularity**: The code is structured into separate files, allowing for easy modification and maintenance.
2. **CSS Variables**: Used for styling, making the theme switching efficient without duplicating styles.
3. **Local Storage**: The theme preference is stored in local storage, ensuring that it persists across page reloads.
4. **Error Handling**: Checks for the existence of the theme toggle button and reports an error if itâ€™s not found.
5. **TypeScript**: Type annotations are used to ensure type safety and improve developer experience.

This implementation covers all requirements and provides a clean, reusable, and modular codebase.